text: Greene County is a county in the U.S. state of Alabama. As of the 2020 census, the population was 7,730; it was the least populous county in Alabama. The county seat is Eutaw. It was named in honor of Revolutionary War General Nathanael Greene of Rhode Island. In the 2020 census, the county's population was 80.8% African-American. == References == Category:Alabama counties Category:1819 establishments in Alabama
title: Greene County, Alabama
